'''{{NAMESPACE}}:{{BASEPAGENAME}}''' generates an external link to a person's profile at [[ResearchGate]].

== Usage ==
One parameter:
: <code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | ''ID'' }}</code>
: <code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= ''ID'' }}</code>

Two parameters:
: <code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | ''ID'' | ''NAME'' }}</code>
: <code><nowiki>{{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= ''ID'' | name= ''NAME'' }}</code>

== Examples ==

===One parameter===
This parameter will be the ID string used in the [[统一资源定位符|URL]] at ResearchGate. When one parameter is used, the [[锚文本|link text]] is the title of the Wikipedia article where the template is used.

''URL:''
: <kbd><nowiki>http://</nowiki>www.researchgate.net/profile/{{hilite|jon_doe}}</kbd>
''Usage:''
: <code><nowiki>* {{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | jon_doe }}</code>
: <code><nowiki>* {{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= jon_doe }}</code>
''Output:''
:* {{{{BASEPAGENAME}} | jon_doe }}
:* {{{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= jon_doe }}

The lead name will change according to the name of the Wikipedia page used on.

===Two parameters===
The first parameter will be the ID string used in the [[统一资源定位符|URL]] at ResearchGate. The second parameter will be used at the [[锚文本|link text]].

''URL:''
: <kbd><nowiki>http://</nowiki>www.researchgate.net/profile/{{hilite|jon_doe}}</kbd>
''Usage:''
: <code><nowiki>* {{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | jon_doe | Jon Doe }}</code>
: <code><nowiki>* {{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= jon_doe | name= Jon Doe }}</code>
''Output:''
:* {{{{BASEPAGENAME}} | jon_doe | Jon Doe }}
:* {{{{BASEPAGENAME}} | id= jon_doe | name= Jon Doe }}

=== No parameters and Wikidata property not defined ===
''Usage:''
: <code><nowiki>* {{</nowiki>{{BASEPAGENAME}}<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code>
''Output:''
:* {{ {{BASEPAGENAME}} }}

